Syntax: bond <weapon>              - Bond to a sword
        bond status                - View bond details
        bond track <name>          - Choose a track (edge/guard/keen/spirit)
        bond track <name> confirm  - Switch tracks (resets rank and points)
        bond rankup                - Spend bond points to advance rank
        bond mastery               - Unlock mastery at max rank (100 qp)
        bond name <new name>       - Rename your bonded weapon
        bond tracks                - List all available tracks

A swordsman can forge a soul-bond with a sword, creating a weapon that
grows alongside them. The bonded weapon automatically scales to the
wielder's current level, but its power budget is determined by the
original weapon's level at the time of bonding. A level 150 sword
produces a far more powerful bond than a level 1 sword.

Only one weapon can be bonded at a time. Bonding a new weapon destroys
the old one and inflicts a "Broken Bond" debuff (reduced hitroll and
damroll for several ticks). All accumulated bond points and track
progress are lost.

Bonded weapons cannot be dropped, given away, disarmed, or lost on
death. They remain equipped through death.

Requirements:
  - Must be a Swordsman (any level).
  - Weapon must be a sword (slash type).
  - Must be holding the weapon.

Bond points are earned by killing mobs while wielding the bonded
weapon. Higher-level mobs relative to the wielder yield more points.
Use bond points to advance your chosen track's rank.

See also: bond tracks bond mastery
